The paper deals with the design of optimal information structures in Bayesian games, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). It also involves the use of algorithms and complexity theory to analyze the computational complexity of optimal signaling, which suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the role of a market maker and the use of objective functions, which suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of computational complexity, which suggests a connection to computational complexity theory (cs.CC).
